The elusive John/John seems to have two views on just about everything...that is, except maybe where John Edwards should get his own views.
 
 
 "Honor the solitude and beauty of wilderness areas and our National Parks by keeping snowmobiles and jet skis out of Yellowstone.... John Kerry will reinstate the Clinton Administration's phase-out of noisy and direct snowmobiles that have been overrunning some of our most precious lands, including Yellowstone National Park and Grand Teton National Park." --John Kerry for President website 
 
 "It is so important that we preserve our rural way of life.... And that includes, making sure...that your right, your ability to hunt and fish is protected; making sure that you can go in the national parks and national forests and ride on a snowmobile." --John Edwards 
 
 Memo to the No. 2 John: Visit JohnKerry.com for your position on this issue.
